2025-09-29 11:27:17,373 - INFO - Strategy Summary: In the given experimental data, lower pipetting speeds and longer wait times, particularly at aspiration, seem to correlate with lower deviation and variability. However, there is a trade-off between accuracy and efficiency. The recommendations aim to balance these factors while also exploring slightly different parameter combinations.
2025-09-29 11:27:17,382 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 1:
2025-09-29 11:27:17,382 - INFO -   Confidence Level: medium
2025-09-29 11:27:17,382 - INFO -   Reasoning: This recommendation is based on the observed correlation between lower speeds (higher speed values since speed is inversely proportional) and lower deviation and variability. The third trial with an aspirate speed of 25 and dispense speed of 17 had the lowest deviation but a slightly higher variability, while the fourth trial with speeds of 16 and 30 had a slightly higher deviation but lower variability. Choosing a middle ground between these speeds might result in a balance of low deviation and low variability. The wait times, air volumes, and overaspirate volumes are averages of the corresponding values in these trials.
2025-09-29 11:27:17,383 - INFO -   Expected Improvement: A reduction in both deviation and variability is expected, although the exact values will depend on other factors like the specific properties of the glycerol used and the accuracy of the pipetting device.
2025-09-29 11:27:17,384 - INFO - LLM Recommendation 2:
2025-09-29 11:27:17,384 - INFO -   Confidence Level: low
2025-09-29 11:27:17,384 - INFO -   Reasoning: This recommendation is a more exploratory one, based on the observed correlation between higher wait times (specifically at aspiration) and lower deviation. The third trial, which had the longest aspirate wait time, had the lowest deviation. However, since there is a trade-off between accuracy and efficiency, the dispense wait time has been reduced to try and offset the increased time taken at aspiration. The air volumes and overaspirate volumes are set to slightly different values to see if a more asymmetrical approach might yield better results.
2025-09-29 11:27:17,385 - INFO -   Expected Improvement: A reduction in deviation is expected, but the variability and time might be slightly higher due to the longer aspirate wait time.
